The paper focuses on studying user behavior on a biomedical ontology repository, which involves information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as data mining. The study also involves analyzing user interactions with the website, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the characteristics of ontologies, which are often stored and managed in databases (DB). Finally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in deep learning (DL) research.
